body:
@micolous Thanks.

The change looks good overall, but the tests are failing (https://travis-ci.org/apache/libcloud/builds/14792563).

Please fix the failing tests and add a new one which tests that `application/octet-stream` is specified if we can't guess the content_type ourselves.

@Jc2k Ah, that's actually a good point & catch. For consistency, `ex_create_keypair` should only take a `name` argument, right?

I do need to admit, that I find the existing API slightly "weird", but it's what we have at the moment and we should follow it for the consistency reasons.

In any case, if we want to change this and get rid of the "import" methods, we should do it now, before the 1.0 release.

@thanatos Yep, thanks for this pull request.

@briancurtin @thanatos The pull request looks good, but I would prefer if you would spent some more time on this and implement `iterate_*` methods.

You have already done the hard part and implementing `iterate_*` methods at this point mostly means shuffling some code around. You can find some examples of how to do that in a recent pull request - https://github.com/apache/libcloud/pull/175 & https://github.com/apache/libcloud/pull/187
